Number 1403
Name Tavern
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 1403
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
From the appearance, this used to be a fine place to spend a quiet evening
or have a rousing drink. Now, it is a place to scrounge firewood. Tables
doors and all woodwork is smashed. Behind the bar, precious and expensive
glass is in piles on the floor. The only thing that isn't a total ruin,
is the overhead pewter mug rack, and that's because it is only hooks on a
beam.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 204
ITEM 1 1312 LIT
ITEM 2 65 VAL2=1409 UNLOCKED
ITEM 3 65 VAL2=1404 UNLOCKED
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
This room is always loaded in the game. You are more than welcome (if not
encouraged) to come in any time to roleplay. It is IMPERATIVE that you save
your character here, so when you leave, come here and EXIT, not disconnect.
I hope you enjoy yourselves here.

Note: If you don't have access to board 24 yet, email Druid for access.
If you have multiple accounts, specify which account gets access.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
Number 1404
Name Kitchen
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CHANNEL 1403
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The kitchen was a total shambles when you moved in but when Aletea took
it upon herself to do the cooking, it was soon moving towards sparkling.
A large number of dented pots, pans and skillets are in the the northeast
corner, on a ruined table, awaiting undenting. Two other tables have been
pieced together and are in use. A pair of large brick ovens, one with a
roaster, one not, are against the west wall, neither in great shape. On
the south wall, there is a wash basin with a lever for running water, and
a door going to the dining room. A door on the west wall, and a pair on
the east wall, lead to the tavern, the pantry and Great Hall, as you turn
to your right. You see Aletea bustling about the place.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 91
EXTEND 0 that has been patched and repaired
ITEM 1 91
ITEM 2 342
EXTEND 2 which just been fixed
ITEM 3 342
ITEM 4 65 VAL2=1403 CLOSED UNLOCKED
ITEM 5 65 VAL2=1175 UNLOCKED
ITEM 6 65 VAL2=1406 UNLOCKED
ITEM 7 65 VAL2=1405 UNLOCKED
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
You see a somewhat stocked pantry. Some of the shelves are smashed, but
there isn't enough food to fill the intact ones.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFSAY Hello?
        ECHO ALL Aletea beams 'Hello! Nice to see you again, %n. Have you finished all your chores yet?'
ENDIF
IFSAY Havenspire?
        ECHO ALL Aletea says 'Yes, Havenspire isn't the most glamorous new home, but we're all going to work to make it home.'
ENDIF
IFSAY Kitchen?
        ECHO ALL 'Well,', Aletea muses, 'it certainly was a lot worse when we got here, but it needs work.'
        ECHO ALL 'Desmark did such a fine job fixing my ovens, now we can use both. I just wish we had food for both!'
ENDIF
IFSAY Food?
        ECHO ALL Aletea frowns, 'Yes, food. We need a lot more than we have.%cWe have enough for a few more weeks, but after that it's going to be rough.'
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 5
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER Why do you want to go in the pantry? It's just smashed and empty.
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
You see a smashed and empty pantry.
*DESCRIPTION_END
