used for storing odd pieces of equipment and supplies that don't have
homes yet.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
Number 1164
Name Carpenter's Woodshop
REGION 20
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
FLETCHER
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is Faricia's second home as she labors to repair the damage to the
woodwork of the keep. In a large bin marked 'TEMPLATES', there are
examples of the pieces used to make a standard shutter and door for the
keep. Against one wall is a large workbench with tools of all sorts on
a wall rack above it. Faricia is at her workbench, working on a section
of the main gate.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 1161
IFSAY Hello?
        ECHO ALL Faricia says distractedly 'Hi there.'
ENDIF
IFSAY Work?
        ECHO ALL Faricia says 'Yes, I'm working on replacing the gate.'%cFarcia shaves a few pieces off one of the pieces.
ENDIF
IFSAY Repairs?
        ECHO ALL Faricia smiles wearily 'Yes, there are a few. I'm training a few people who will be able to%cmake shutters and doors for us while I do other things.'
ENDIF
IFSAY Wood?
        ECHO ALL Faricia ponders 'Well, we have some, but always need more.'
ENDIF
;
