IFPREVERB GO 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You go down into the storage room, do what you need to do and come back.
        ECHO OTHERS %N disappears down the trapdoor, reappearing shortly.
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
You peer down the trapdoor, looking into the storage room. Huge bags of wool
and cotton against one wall, while bolts of homespun cloth are here as well.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
Number 1166
Name Brewery
REGION 20
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room has one fermenting tank at the far end and a trio of moderate-sized
conditioning kegs are in a rack in a hollow in the ground near them. Piping
runs from the back of the kegs to below the ground. Sealed kegs labeled
"Malted Barley" are against a wall. On a drying rack are some cone-shaped
flowers. There are a few jars with spices in them, such as cinnamon and
nutmeg on a desk filled with recipes and brewing records.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 1162
;
Number 1167
Name Forge
REGION 20
FORGE
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Two seconds after you walk in the door, you feel like you are in another
world; one which is hot, grimy and dark. The only light is from the glowing
of embers in the forge and from a pair of dim lanterns. A pair of huge anvils
sit near the forge, and a wall rack nearby holds tools. On the far side of
the forge is a smelting setup.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
Number 1168
Name Outside the Fence,
REGION 20
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The rust-colored mat of pine needles muffles your footfalls as you walk
through the forest, and you startle more than one squirrel into an angry
chattering. The thick foliage blocks much of the sun from the forest floor,
preventing thick undergrowth and stunting the development of what there is.
You notice knobs and stretches of rock poking through the thin soil; the
roots of the mountain beginning in this forest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1169
EXIT S 1171
;
Number 1169
Name Outside the Fence
REGION 20
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You come to a small clearing of sorts in the thick gathering of oaks and
maples. A blue-grey boulder with a flat top the size of a large wagon has
forced the trees around it to open a rent in the canopy of foliage overhead.
Several types of small flowers have taken advantage of the single shaft of
sunlight beaming down upon the rockface, rooting themselves tenaciously in
the cracked stone and stretching translucent petals to the light. You catch
the flash of russet fur as some forest animal flees its favorite sunbathing
spot at your approach.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1168
EXIT E 1170
;
Number 1170
Name Outside the Fence, Mountain Slope
REGION 20
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
It is difficult to walk without leaning into the slope of the mountain. Above
your head, thick pine boughs shut out much of the light, and their fallen
needles make the sloping ground slippery and dangerous. Fortunately, the pine
trees grow close together, allowing you to inch gingerly from one tree trunk
to the next.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 1172
EXIT W 1169
;
Number 1171
Name Road Outside Fence
REGION 20
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The road leading to the keep is fairly smooth gravel. To the west, the
road heads towards the forest, where it forks, and to the east is the
scorched and battered stockade gate. North of the road is the primary
field that farmers are planting, while on the other side is the one that
is only half cleared.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1421
EXIT N 1168
EXIT S 1173
ITEM 0 68 VAL2=1160 UNLOCKED
ITEM 1 1325
ITEM 2 1325
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The large field before you has been well-turned by a dedicated team of plough
men working in tandem from dawn to dusk. The smell of the dark earth is rich
and heavy in your nostrils, reminding you of growing things, sparking a hope
for new life. Deep within the furrows the earth is still moist, but the sun
has dried the mounds of earth beside the furrows to a lighter color dirt that
crumbles easily beneath your feet. Large rocks removed from the path of the
plow line the perimeter of the field in a low stone wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
This second field, though still overgrown with grasses and low bushes in one
half, is well on its way to being readied for planting. In the distance you
can see a team of large draft animals hitched to a plow waiting patiently as
a few men wrestle a large rock out of their path. You can see by the rich
dark color of the soil that this field holds as much promise as the first of
an abundant harvest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
Number 1172
Name Outside the Fence, Mountain Slope
REGION 20
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Your calf muscles burn as you climb the steep mountain slope between pines, oaks,
and maples. This area is particularly treacherous because of a fall of loose
rock and scree, probably originating from higher up on the mountain, scattered
between the trees. It looks as though one ill-placed foot could set the whole
slide to falling again, bringing its luckless disturber with it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1170
EXIT S 1419
;
Number 1173
Name Outside the Fence, Tent City
REGION 20
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The long grass of the field has been well-trampled down, and a tent city has
sprung up in its place like some bizarre form of mushroom. Tents of all shapes
and sizes, in leather and wool and canvas, sprawl in haphazard lines across the
field with no apparent regard for order. Many of the temporary homes are
ragged and much-patched, some worn thin in places, others sagging tiredly
from their splintered poles as if without hope. Despite this, many of the
gaunt-faced people you see as you walk through hold a new spark in their eyes,
some of them even smiling when their eyes fall on the shape of the keep in the
distance.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1171
EXIT E 1174
;
Number 1174
Name Outside the Fence, Tent City
REGION 20
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A bluish haze of smoke hangs over the sprawl of tents in the field as people
cook their meals and perform various other chores, their haunted but hope-
ful eyes lifting often to the keep across the field. Children, their bound-
less spirits not subdued by anything for long, run laughing among the tents
in games of hide and seek,sometimes wringing a sad smile from an elder.
You notice that many of the tents are in sad repair, some composed merely
of a few blankets stretched across poles, and wonder at the courage of the
people who endure such conditions.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1173
EXIT E 1419
